trans-unit.source: Using Diagnostic Search in Application Insights
trans-unit.target: Using Diagnostic Search in Application Insights

trans-unit.source: Diagnostic Search is the blade in [Application Insights][start] that you use to find and explore individual telemetry items, such as page views, exceptions, or web requests.
trans-unit.target: Diagnostic Search is the blade in [Application Insights][start] that you use to find and explore individual telemetry items, such as page views, exceptions, or web requests.

trans-unit.source: And you can view log traces and events that you have coded.
trans-unit.target: And you can view log traces and events that you have coded.

trans-unit.source: When do you see Diagnostic Search?
trans-unit.target: When do you see Diagnostic Search?

trans-unit.source: You can open diagnostic search explicitly:
trans-unit.target: You can open diagnostic search explicitly:

trans-unit.source: Open diagnostic search
trans-unit.target: Open diagnostic search

trans-unit.source: It also opens when you click through some charts and grid items.
trans-unit.target: It also opens when you click through some charts and grid items.

trans-unit.source: In this case, its filters are pre-set to focus on the type of item you selected.
trans-unit.target: In this case, its filters are pre-set to focus on the type of item you selected.

trans-unit.source: For example, if your application is a web service, the overview blade shows a chart of volume of requests.
trans-unit.target: For example, if your application is a web service, the overview blade shows a chart of volume of requests.

trans-unit.source: Click it and you get to a more detailed chart, with a listing showing how many requests have been made for each URL.
trans-unit.target: Click it and you get to a more detailed chart, with a listing showing how many requests have been made for each URL.

trans-unit.source: Click any row, and you get a list of the individual requests for that URL:
trans-unit.target: Click any row, and you get a list of the individual requests for that URL:

trans-unit.source: Open diagnostic search
trans-unit.target: Open diagnostic search

trans-unit.source: The main body of Diagnostic Search is a list of telemetry items - server requests, page views, custom events that you have coded, and so on.
trans-unit.target: The main body of Diagnostic Search is a list of telemetry items - server requests, page views, custom events that you have coded, and so on.

trans-unit.source: At the top of the list is a summary chart showing counts of events over time.
trans-unit.target: At the top of the list is a summary chart showing counts of events over time.

trans-unit.source: Events typically show up in diagnostic search before they appear in metric explorer.
trans-unit.target: Events typically show up in diagnostic search before they appear in metric explorer.

trans-unit.source: Although the blade refreshes itself at intervals, you can click Refresh if you're waiting for a particular event.
trans-unit.target: Although the blade refreshes itself at intervals, you can click Refresh if you're waiting for a particular event.

trans-unit.source: Inspect individual items
trans-unit.target: Inspect individual items

trans-unit.source: Select any telemetry item to see key fields and related items.
trans-unit.target: Select any telemetry item to see key fields and related items.

trans-unit.source: If you want to see the full set of fields, click "...".
trans-unit.target: If you want to see the full set of fields, click "...".

trans-unit.source: Open diagnostic search
trans-unit.target: Open diagnostic search

trans-unit.source: To find the full set of fields, use plain strings (without wildcards).
trans-unit.target: To find the full set of fields, use plain strings (without wildcards).

trans-unit.source: The available fields depend on the type of telemetry.
trans-unit.target: The available fields depend on the type of telemetry.

trans-unit.source: Filter event types
trans-unit.target: Filter event types

trans-unit.source: Open the Filter blade and choose the event types you want to see.
trans-unit.target: Open the Filter blade and choose the event types you want to see.

trans-unit.source: (If, later, you want to restore the filters with which you opened the blade, click Reset.)
trans-unit.target: (If, later, you want to restore the filters with which you opened the blade, click Reset.)

trans-unit.source: Choose Filter and select telemetry types
trans-unit.target: Choose Filter and select telemetry types

trans-unit.source: The event types are:
trans-unit.target: The event types are:

trans-unit.source: **Trace** - Diagnostic logs including TrackTrace, log4Net, NLog, and System.Diagnostic.Trace calls.
trans-unit.target: **Trace** - Diagnostic logs including TrackTrace, log4Net, NLog, and System.Diagnostic.Trace calls.

trans-unit.source: **Request** - HTTP requests received by your server application, including pages, scripts, images, style files and data.
trans-unit.target: **Request** - HTTP requests received by your server application, including pages, scripts, images, style files and data.

trans-unit.source: These events are used to create the request and response overview charts.
trans-unit.target: These events are used to create the request and response overview charts.

trans-unit.source: **Page View** - Telemetry sent by the web client, used to create page view reports.
trans-unit.target: **Page View** - Telemetry sent by the web client, used to create page view reports.

trans-unit.source: **Custom Event** - If you inserted calls to TrackEvent() in order to [monitor usage][track], you can search them here.
trans-unit.target: **Custom Event** - If you inserted calls to TrackEvent() in order to [monitor usage][track], you can search them here.

trans-unit.source: **Exception** - Uncaught exceptions in the server, and those that you log by using TrackException().
trans-unit.target: **Exception** - Uncaught exceptions in the server, and those that you log by using TrackException().

trans-unit.source: Filter on property values
trans-unit.target: Filter on property values

trans-unit.source: You can filter events on the values of their properties.
trans-unit.target: You can filter events on the values of their properties.

trans-unit.source: The available properties depend on the event types you selected.
trans-unit.target: The available properties depend on the event types you selected.

trans-unit.source: For example, pick out requests with a specific response code.
trans-unit.target: For example, pick out requests with a specific response code.

trans-unit.source: Expand a property and choose a value
trans-unit.target: Expand a property and choose a value

trans-unit.source: Choosing no values of a particular property has the same effect as choosing all values; it switches off filtering on that property.
trans-unit.target: Choosing no values of a particular property has the same effect as choosing all values; it switches off filtering on that property.

trans-unit.source: Narrow your search
trans-unit.target: Narrow your search

trans-unit.source: Notice that the counts to the right of the filter values show how many occurrences there are in the current filtered set.
trans-unit.target: Notice that the counts to the right of the filter values show how many occurrences there are in the current filtered set.

trans-unit.source: Q & A
trans-unit.target: Q & A

trans-unit.source: How much data is retained?
trans-unit.target: How much data is retained?

trans-unit.source: Up to 500 events per second from each application.
trans-unit.target: Up to 500 events per second from each application.

trans-unit.source: Events are retained for seven days.
trans-unit.target: Events are retained for seven days.

trans-unit.source: How can I see POST data in my server requests?
trans-unit.target: How can I see POST data in my server requests?

trans-unit.source: We don't log the POST data automatically, but you can use [TrackTrace or log calls][trace].
trans-unit.target: We don't log the POST data automatically, but you can use [TrackTrace or log calls][trace].

trans-unit.source: Put the POST data in the message parameter.
trans-unit.target: Put the POST data in the message parameter.

trans-unit.source: You can't filter on the message the way you can properties, but the size limit is longer.
trans-unit.target: You can't filter on the message the way you can properties, but the size limit is longer.
